body:
@bluetech I like the environment variable approach, I didn't think of that.

Your if statements will also work in case any other warning has a ``source`` field. So +1.

I don't think we need to do anything with ``warning_message.source``. It is already represented and there is nothing generic possible with it, except maybe printing ``vars(warning_message.source)``, which only works if it has a ``__dict__``. I think the usefulness is further restricted, because it is already garbage collected, but I'm not sure right now.
